    • Uses of ParsedInstruction in server.project

      Subclasses of ParsedInstruction in server.project 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ParsedCustom
      A ParsedCustom object represents a block of code written by the user, which can be anything: an instruction, a class declaration...
      class  ParsedElse
      A ParsedElse object represents a set of instructions to be executed only if the condition of a ParsedIf doesn't hold.
      class  ParsedFor
      A ParsedFor object represents a set of instructions which has to be repeated a fixed number of times.
      class  ParsedIf
      A ParsedIf object represents a set of instructions which has to be executed only if a certain condition is satisfied.
      class  ParsedReturn
      A ParsedReturn object represents a statement of a ParsedMethod telling it to exit and return the control to the caller.
      class  ParsedStatement
      A ParsedStatement object is a ParsedInstruction representing an action to be performed on a specific variable.
      class  ParsedWhile
      A ParsedWhile object represents a set of instructions which has to be repeated until a certain condition holds.
